- verification of conductive and radiative heat transfer in a small pebble bed

- P1 used as a radiaton model

- temperature-sensitive thermal conductivity of the pebbles

- vacuum conditions

- temperature profile tested against a view-factor--based numerical solution
  (Tausendschoen and Radl, Int. J. Heat Mass Transfer, 2021)
  and experimental measurements (De Beer, 2014)

- pseudo-scattering used for the removal of heat flux fluctuations

- more details in Macak, Goniva, Radl "Predictions of the P1 approximation for 
  radiative heat transfer in heterogeneous granular media" (2022)
